===Etymology===
{{bor|en|grc|μισόθεος||hating the gods}}, from {{compound|grc|μίσος|t1=hatred|θεός|t2=god|nocat=1}}. The Greek compound is found in Aeschylus (''Agamemnon'' 1090; compare {{m|en|dystheism}}). The English word appears as a nonce-coinage, used by T. De Quincey in 1846.

